sentences: Jan Zdeněk Bartoš (4 June 1908, Dvůr Králové nad Labem – 1 June 1981, Prague) was a Czech composer.
Jan Zdeněk Bartoš (4 June 1908, Dvůr Králové nad Labem – 1 June 1981, Prague) was a Czech composer.
Jan Zdeněk Bartoš (4 June 1908, Dvůr Králové nad Labem – 1 June 1981, Prague) was a Czech composer.
Bartoš started to play the violin as a pupil of Karel Hršel in Hradec Králové.
Bartoš started to play the violin as a pupil of Karel Hršel in Hradec Králové.
In 1924, after he graduated from business school, Bartoš left for France.
From 1929 to 1931 he travelled with that company to Africa, Asia and Madagascar.
He graduated in 1943.
From 1956 he worked at the Czech Ministry of Education and taught composition and music theory at the Prague Conservatory.
His work was also part of the music event in the art competition at the 1948 Summer Olympics.
